# terminal-based todo list

todo list entries have

- number
- description
- status (done, not done)

## usage

- add <description> (add a new todo list entry, print the number)
- list (list all todo list entries)
- done <number> (mark todo list entry as done)
- undone <number> (mark todo list entry as not done)
- remove <number> (remove todo list entry)

## storage

todo list entries are stored in `~/.todo` as json
